{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:sirach.27",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 27,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 27 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.27.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:1",
      "text": "Many have sinned for profit. He who seeks to multiply wealth will turn his eye away.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.27.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:2",
      "text": "As a nail will stick fast between the joinings of stones, so sin will thrust itself in between buying and selling.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.27.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:3",
      "text": "Unless a person holds on diligently to the fear of the Lord, his house will be overthrown quickly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.27.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:4",
      "text": "In the shaking of a sieve, the refuse remains, so does the filth of man in his thoughts.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.27.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:5",
      "text": "The furnace tests the potter’s vessels; so the test of a person is in his thoughts.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.27.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:6",
      "text": "The fruit of a tree discloses its cultivation, so is the utterance of the thought of a person’s heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.27.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:7",
      "text": "Praise no man before you hear his thoughts, for this is how people are tested.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.27.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:8",
      "text": "If you follow righteousness, you will obtain it, and put it on like a long robe of glory.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.27.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:9",
      "text": "Birds will return to their own kind, so truth will return to those who practice it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.27.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:10",
      "text": "The lion lies in wait for prey. So does sin for those who do evil.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.27.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:11",
      "text": "The discourse of a godly man is always wise, but the fool changes like the moon.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.27.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:12",
      "text": "Limit your time among people void of understanding, but persevere among the thoughtful.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.27.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:13",
      "text": "The talk of fools is offensive. Their laughter is wantonly sinful.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.27.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:14",
      "text": "Their talk with much swearing makes hair stand upright. Their strife makes others plug their ears.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.27.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:15",
      "text": "The strife of the proud leads to bloodshed. Their abuse of each other is a grievous thing to hear.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.27.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:16",
      "text": "He who reveals secrets destroys trust, and will not find a close friend.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.27.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:17",
      "text": "Love a friend, and keep faith with him; but if you reveal his secrets, you shall not follow him;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.27.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:18",
      "text": "for as a man has destroyed his enemy, so you have destroyed the friendship of your neighbor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.27.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:19",
      "text": "As a bird which you have released out of your hand, so you have let your neighbor go, and you will not catch him again.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.27.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:20",
      "text": "Don’t pursue him, for he has gone far away, and has escaped like a gazelle out of the snare.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.27.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:21",
      "text": "For a wound may be bound up, and after abuse there may be reconciliation; but he who reveals secrets is without hope.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.27.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:22",
      "text": "One who winks the eye contrives evil things; and those who know him will keep their distance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.27.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:23",
      "text": "When you are present, he will speak sweetly, and will admire your words; but afterward he will twist his speech and set a trap in your words.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.27.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:24",
      "text": "I have hated many things, but nothing like him. The Lord will hate him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.27.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:25",
      "text": "One who casts a stone straight up casts it on his own head. A deceitful blow opens wounds.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.27.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:26",
      "text": "He who digs a pit will fall into it. He who sets a snare will be caught in it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.27.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:27",
      "text": "He who does evil things, they will roll back upon him, and he will not know where they came from.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.27.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:28",
      "text": "Mockery and reproach are from the arrogant. Vengeance lies in wait for them like a lion.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.27.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:29",
      "text": "Those who rejoice at the fall of the godly will be caught in a snare. Anguish will consume them before they die.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.27.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 27:30",
      "text": "Wrath and anger, these also are abominations. A sinner will possess them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
